      "SummaryText": "appropriate.  \n\nREVISIONS\n\nThis RMP Plan was submitted as a correction on September 3, 2019. The reason for correction was to update the company name and email domain name in Section 1 and this Executive Summary from Univar USA Inc. to Univar Solutions USA Inc.  In late February 2019, Univar USA Inc. purchased the assets of Nexeo Solutions LLC.  Effective September 1, 2019, the assets of Nexeo Solutions LLC were transferred to Univar USA Inc. and the legal name of Univar USA Inc. changed to Univar Solutions USA Inc. There was no material change in the day-to-day operations and personnel overseeing compliance under the above referenced facility. The purchase of Nexeo Solutions LLC's assets and company name change do not constitute a transfer of ownership for the above referenced facility address.\n\n12/21/2020. Increased Chlorine maximum quantity and updated some dates in Section 7.\n\n10/4/2023. Increased Chlorine maximum quantity and updated some dates in Section 7 and 9.\n\nThis RMP Plan was submitted as a correction on January 6, 2024. The reason for correction was to update the company name in Section 1 and this Executive Summary from Univar Solutions USA Inc. to Univar Solutions USA LLC.\n\n6/18/2024. Submission removed formaldehyde from the RMP Plan as the facility no longer stores this chemical above the RMP Plan threshold quantity.  Also removed the anhydrous ammonia worst case release of 160,000 lbs which represented receiving a railcar of anhydrous ammonia.  The facility no longer receives this chemical via railcar.  Population estimates using 2020 census data and the off-site consequence analysis were also updated in this revision."
    },
