      "ESSeqNum": 1,
      "FacilityID": 1000115345,
      "SummaryText": "ponders in the event of all other incidents.\n\nUnivar Solutions invites and encourages local emergency responders such as the fire department to visit and familiarize themselves with Univar Solutions products and facilities.  Joint emergency exercises are conducted when possible.\n\nSTATIONARY SOURCE\n\nThe Providence Harborside facility stores, handles, and delivers a variety of hazardous and non-hazardous chemical products to wholesale customers in New England. In addition, bleach and dilute ammonia solutions are also processed and distributed. The facility handles formaldehyde solution, chlorine, anhydrous ammonia and aqueous ammonia solutions above the threshold planning quantity limits. \n\nGENERAL PREVENTION PROGRAM AND CHEMICAL SPECIFIC PREVENTION STEPS\nAs outlined previously, Univar Solutions is subject to OSHA's Process Safety Management regulation and utilizes this program to meet the prevention program requirements under RMP.\n\nChemical-specific prevention steps include the following:\n1. The maintenance of minimal practical inventories.\n2. Employee training and operating procedures.\n3. Employee release detection and mitigation activities.\n4. Equipment and containers designed to meet appropriate regulatory guidelines  \n\n\nACCIDENT HISTORY\nThe facility has experienced no accidents as specified in 40 CFR Part 68 related to the containerized storage and handling of RMP chemicals in the previous 5 years.\n\nEMERGENCY RESPONSE PROGRAM\nAn emergency contingency plan has been prepared and made available to local emergency response agencies.  The Providence Fire Department is familiar with and periodically visits the site.  The facility can utilize local emergency response contractors to provide onsite and offsite emergency response services in the event of a release.\n\nPLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY\nAt this time, the facility does not have specific plans to improve safety.  However, we are continuously evaluating our processes and will implement any safety improvements as"
