      "SummaryText": "RMP PLAN\n\nEXECUTIVE SUMMARY\n\nCOMPANY OVERVIEW\n\nUnivar Solutions USA LLC (dba Univar Solutions) is a wholesale chemical distributor serving a wide variety of U.S. industries.  Founded in 1924, Univar Solutions supplies the water and waste water industry, food industry, compounders, pharmaceuticals, mining, forest products, oil and gas producers, electronics, coatings and many other key industries with the chemical raw materials required to produce or refine products utilized in numerous end-use markets.\n\nUnivar Solutions is a member of the National Association of Chemical Distributors (NACD) and complies with the Responsible Distribution Process (RDP), an environmental, health and safety improvement initiative.\n\nSome of the products stored and handled by this Univar Solutions facility are subject to EPA's Risk Management Program rule (40 CFR Part 68).  A key requirement of this rule is the preparation and submission of an RMP Plan, contained herein. The contents of the RMP plan are prescribed by EPA, including this Executive Summary.\n\nCORPORATE PREVENTION AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE APPROACH\n\n\nPREVENTION PROGRAM\nProcesses that are subject to OSHA's Process Safety management (PSM) standard AND are regulated under EPA's RMP rule are subject to the Program 3 Prevention program.  Univar Solutions has documented the Prevention Program in its Process Safety Management Manual. Briefly, this program includes provisions and requirements for:\n\n* Process Safety Information\n* Process Hazard Analysis\n* Operating Procedures\n* Training\n* Mechanical Integrity\n* Management of Change\n* Pre-Startup Review\n* Compliance Audits\n* Incident Investigation\n* Employee Participation\n* Hot Work permits\n* Contractors\n\nEMERGENCY RESPONSE APPROACH\n\nUnivar Solutions has an Emergency Contingency Plan in place.  This Plan is shared with local emergency responders who have access to Univar Solutions facility personnel.  Univar Solutions responds to minor incidents but will call in professional emergency res"
